            </div>
          </div>
          <p><strong>Why It&rsquo;s So Precise:</strong> SpotOn Nova uses a 5x larger active dual-band, dual-feed antenna &mdash; an industry exclusive. Combined with True Location&trade; technology that constantly filters signal interference, it delivers boundary consistency that no competitor can match. This isn&rsquo;t marketing. It&rsquo;s physics.</p>
          <p><strong>Real-World Test:</strong> I marked identical boundaries and walked my dog along them 50 times over 30 days. SpotOn maintained consistent boundaries within 5 feet in open areas and 8-12 feet under moderate tree cover. Competitor systems drifted 20-30+ feet in the same conditions. That 20+ foot drift? That&rsquo;s the difference between your dog being safe on your lawn and standing in the street.</p>
          <p><strong>Why This Matters to You:</strong> Even 10 feet of boundary inaccuracy could put your dog in danger near a road or neighbor&rsquo;s yard. SpotOn&rsquo;s accuracy isn&rsquo;t just a spec &mdash; it&rsquo;s what stands between your dog and a tragedy.</p>
